        "apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/profile/francisbeckett",
        "bio":"<p>Francis Beckett is an author, journalist, broadcaster and contemporary historian. He is the author of <a href=\"http://www.bitebackpublishing.com/books/What%20did%20the%20Baby%20Boomers%20ever%20do%20for%20us/\">What Did the Baby Boomers Ever Do for Us?</a> Earlier books include history of the 1884-5 miners's strike, written with the Guardian's Westminster correspondent David Hencke, biographies of four prime ministers: Attlee, Macmillan, Blair and Brown, and a book about education, The Great City Academy Fraud.<br />Before going freelance he worked as a trade union editor and a Labour party press officer and was president of the National Union of Journalists, an organiser for the housing charity Shelter and head of press and publications at the National Union of Students.<br />His website can be found <br /><a href=\"http://www.francisbeckett.co.uk\">here</a></p>",
