            "apiUrl": "http://content.guardianapis.com/profile/jonathandavidfarley",
            "bio": "<p>Jonathan Farley is a <a href=\"http://www.latticetheory.net/\">professor of mathematics</a>, and member of <a href=\"http://www.thewarrengroup.biz/\">the Warren Group</a>, campaign advisers of <a href=\"http://www.alvingreeneforussenator.com/\">Alvin Greene</a>, the <a href=\"http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2010/07/26/alvin-greene-gets-most-media-attention/\">Democratic party's nominee for US Senate in South Carolina</a>. Born in Rochester, New York, Jonathan obtained his doctorate in maths at Oxford University in 1995, and was, during 2001-2002, a Fulbright distinguished scholar in the UK. After various visiting scholarships, fellowships and professorships at numerous academic institutions, including Caltech, Stanford, Harvard and MIT, Jonathan gained tenure at Vanderbilt University, Tennessee in 2003; however, after <a href=\"http://www.wienerzeitung.at/DesktopDefault.aspx?TabID=4103&amp;Alias=wzo&amp;cob=524654\">receiving death threats from Ku Klux Klan-supporting terrorists</a>, Jonathan was obliged to flee his home and job in Tennessee</p>",
